{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2efea085-c464-4862-858c-6fc1fead82ef","content":"Since you're using **Microsoft.Testing.Platform**, hang detection is built in. Just pass the `--hang-dump-timeout` flag:\n\n```\ndotnet test --hang-dump-timeout 5m\n```\n\nThis will automatically terminate and report any test that hangs for more than 5 minutes. You can also add `--hang-dump-type mini` or `--hang-dump-type full` to capture a dump file for debugging.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1c3293fb-3614-445a-a6ae-7cac9f78956a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"This is using MSTest with Microsoft.Testing.Platform runner. To add a 5-minute hang timeout, I can use the `--hang-dump-timeout` option when running `dotnet test`, or configure it in a `.runsettings` file, or pass it as a command-line argument.\n\nSince they're using Microsoft.Testing.Platform (as specified in global.json), the hang detection is built in. The command-line option is `--hang-dump-timeout 5m`.\n\nLet me show the user how to run tests with the hang timeout.","outputTokens":239},"id":"cc820fd4-806c-4d97-b6b9-ecf434335567","timestamp":"2026-04-07T15:54:19.763Z","parentId":"09915d9d-0fcc-4958-ad01-73c3ab40a45a"}
